main event: A white light was observed moving in the sky over Oklahoma on 10 June 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for a duration of 3 minutes., The object is described as appearing to be about 3-5 feet in diameter., It moved from north to south without leaving a contrail., The observed light did not produce any sound., The object was speculated to resemble a satellite but was moving at a faster speed.
sighted object: one white light moving in the sky
witness description: SSGT - Military and Mrs. Clayton - Civilian
